%% Failure recovery: EtlScheduler catch-up after downtime
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant ES as EtlScheduler<br/>(restarted after downtime)
    participant AUR as Aurora
    participant DW as Cluster DW
    participant IA as IntervalAggregator

    Note over ES: Restart at 14:35 after ~45min downtime
    Note over ES: Last successful interval was 13:45

    ES->>AUR: Interval_GetClusters
    AUR-->>ES: clusters

    loop Per cluster
        ES->>AUR: Interval_GetLastEtlRequest(c, 'COMPOSITE_ETL')
        AUR-->>ES: lastSuccessful = 13:45

        ES->>ES: currentInterval = 14:30 (This15MinIncrement)
        ES->>ES: gap detected: 14:00, 14:15, 14:30 all missing

        loop For each missed slot (14:00 -> 14:15 -> 14:30)
            ES->>DW: IC_GetETLData(...)
            DW-->>ES: etlTime
            alt ETL data exists for slot
                ES->>IA: POST IntervalRequest (catch-up)
                IA-->>ES: 200
                ES->>AUR: Interval_UpdateLastEtlRequest
                ES->>ES: metric etl_interval_count++
            else No ETL data
                ES->>IA: POST ErrorIntervalRequest (skip)
                ES->>ES: metric etl_missed_intervals++
            end
        end
    end

    Note over ES: Normal operation resumes on next 60s tick
